Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,Fullmetal Alchemist,0000,0000,0000,,Brotherhood
Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,Fullmetal Alchemist,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 46
Comment: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,Default,Fullmetal Alchemist,0000,0000,0000,,===============================================================

Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.36,0:01:34.07,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,The forthcoming "Promised Day".
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.10,0:01:40.33,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,People are continuing to prepare for the day that will determine their fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.96,0:01:46.02,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Time passes by, and it is now spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.02,0:01:49.26,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,At last, the Promised Day is about to arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.09,0:01:59.68,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Some sort of festival?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.68,0:02:03.05,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,It's the Festival of the Sheep, a local specialty of Resembool that takes place every spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.89,0:02:07.82,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to ask something like this on an important day, but we'd like to replenish our water supplies.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.82,0:02:08.87,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Sure thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.87,0:02:10.23,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Have all the water you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.52,0:02:12.40,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Bring out the water tanks!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.28,0:02:17.07,Default,Sol2,0000,0000,0000,,One, two...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.81,0:02:18.78,Default,Sol2,0000,0000,0000,,There.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.09,0:02:38.76,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like there's no one home.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.87,0:02:41.09,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Here we are, miss.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.04,0:02:58.49,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Home sweet home.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.58,0:03:07.29,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, this place is full of automails.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.50,0:03:09.40,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't touch the ones that aren't finished yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.02,0:03:23.93,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,It's so dusty in here...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.65,0:03:40.28,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,What happened?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.96,0:03:43.52,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Edward Elric?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.16,0:03:46.20,Default,Gor,0000,0000,0000,,Intruders?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.08,0:03:48.24,Default,Gor,0000,0000,0000,,Oww!!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.98,0:03:51.75,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell are you guys doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.02,0:03:52.94,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Lin?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.90,0:03:56.13,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,If I recall, you two are working for Kimblee!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.13,0:03:56.75,Default,Gor,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.93,0:04:00.63,Default,Gor,0000,0000,0000,,You guys are... from Briggs!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.31,0:04:03.13,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,You chased us all the way down here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.43,0:04:05.88,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! Wait! Wait! Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.88,0:04:06.63,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Put down your guns!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.63,0:04:10.16,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Hey Ed... just {\i1}what{\i0\fscx40} {\r} is going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.16,0:04:12.82,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Long story.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.82,0:04:15.40,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, what were you doing in my room?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.70,0:04:18.57,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I just wanted to eat while enjoying the outside view every once in a while!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.57,0:04:20.73,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,I said, put down your gun!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.73,0:04:22.22,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,Quit yelling!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.85,0:04:24.57,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,This dog is so loud.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.07,0:04:28.61,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Get the hell out of my room!!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.80,0:04:42.25,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,You had me worried sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.86,0:04:43.98,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.98,0:04:46.10,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Glad to see you're safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.10,0:04:48.05,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,A-Al isn't with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.67,0:04:53.02,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Al's at the station!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.02,0:04:54.56,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,He's with Major Miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.28,0:04:56.72,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,But they're about to depart soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.72,0:04:58.58,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,If you hurry, you may be able to make it in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.87,0:05:05.92,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.54,0:05:07.61,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you going to go see him?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.45,0:05:12.92,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We're fugitives wanted by Central.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.16,0:05:16.23,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It would be bad if someone were to see us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.26,0:05:18.36,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.39,0:05:32.22,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,The Festival of the Sheep, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.83,0:05:34.26,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Sure brings back memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.63,0:05:38.08,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,We're going to be departing soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.59,0:05:39.40,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.00,0:05:47.90,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I hope you will have found your body by the next time you return to this town.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.00,0:05:49.98,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.68,0:06:06.86,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,Winry?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.35,0:06:13.43,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome home.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.97,0:06:15.19,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.65,0:06:18.04,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for worrying you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.38,0:06:23.07,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like we have more of you dowdy people in here now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.07,0:06:25.49,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry for causing such a ruckus earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.88,0:06:28.52,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,We're soldiers from Briggs.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.52,0:06:31.24,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,We were dispatched as Miss Winry's bodyguards.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.54,0:06:34.93,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,You're Lin... right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.93,0:06:35.97,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.97,0:06:37.91,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,You know this dude?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.56,0:06:41.88,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,The name's Greed.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.88,0:06:42.96,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet ya.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.49,0:06:45.55,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.91,0:06:54.56,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,And so, these guys are currently working for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.56,0:06:56.31,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,What made you come here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.31,0:06:59.73,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,To make sure his automail's all tuned up and stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.02,0:07:02.21,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,You know, to prepare for the worst.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.21,0:07:03.77,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,Take a look at him later, Winry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.49,0:07:09.40,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,You made all his latest stuff, so I can't do the fine-tuning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.64,0:07:12.95,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, no problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.31,0:07:18.39,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.13,0:07:21.37,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So the people of Lior have gotten back up on their feet again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.05,0:07:23.53,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,That's a relief.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.53,0:07:25.02,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's been bugging me, to tell you the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.09,0:07:31.88,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,So, why is Al with Major Miles?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.46,0:07:36.92,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I heard the people from Briggs are going to do something at the joint exercises in the east.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.44,0:07:41.16,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Al volunteered to join them, saying there might be something he could help out with.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.31,0:07:43.32,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.30,0:07:48.24,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Your dad went to Central ahead of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.61,0:07:53.86,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I heard he's in some slum called 'Kanama', so you should meet up with him to get the details.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.15,0:08:00.97,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,The Promised Day is coming up... right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.72,0:08:06.72,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I heard about that from Greed as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.32,0:08:13.76,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,It's a day when we may be able to get our bodies back,\N or a day when a great tragedy will strike this nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.25,0:08:18.12,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.66,0:08:20.27,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.72,0:08:24.64,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Take Granny and Den and escape to another country.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.06,0:08:28.58,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Are you telling me to run away?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.62,0:08:30.43,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Telling those close to you to escape makes it sound like you've already given up!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.97,0:08:34.06,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you stop the threat to this country?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.06,0:08:35.52,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I'll stop them!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.52,0:08:38.12,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,But there's a one in a million chance that it may not work!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.12,0:08:40.29,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Be 100% sure, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.41,0:08:44.58,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,They're planning to do something terrible, aren't they?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.58,0:08:47.29,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Beat them to a pulp and protect our country!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.75,0:08:52.28,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,And while you're at it, get your bodies back and return safe and sound!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.28,0:08:54.80,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,I'll do {\i1}anything{\i0\fscx40} {\r} to make that happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.04,0:09:03.43,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Geez, you make it sound like a walk in the park.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.64,0:09:04.65,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.65,0:09:07.10,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,You're not acting like yourself-
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.79,0:09:08.86,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Ed!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.86,0:09:12.65,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Gosh, you're such an annoying woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.65,0:09:13.65,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Ed!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.83,0:09:24.20,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,Fine woman you have up there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.59,0:09:27.46,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,She just sounds like she wants everything\Nin the world. Quite the greedy one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.46,0:09:31.24,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,When you get too greedy, it comes back to bite you in the behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.03,0:09:32.86,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,See this?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.86,0:09:35.87,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to bring back the dead, and this was my reward.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.87,0:09:37.20,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,You really think so?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.60,0:09:43.67,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,"I long to see someone who died",\N"I want to be rich", "I want women"...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.67,0:09:45.91,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,"I want to protect the world"...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.91,0:09:47.99,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,They're all desires.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.63,0:09:50.23,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, wishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.42,0:09:55.07,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,If you ask me, there's neither 'right' nor 'wrong' when it comes to greed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.07,0:10:01.19,Default,Greed,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx95}You humans go around ranking certain types of greed in order from good to bad, which makes you so hard to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.73,0:10:12.67,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,You're leaving {\i1}now{\i0\fscx40} {\r} of all times?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.67,0:10:16.76,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,We were planning on leaving today anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.06,0:10:21.78,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for the tune-up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.90,0:10:28.73,Default,Pinako,0000,0000,0000,,If you ever happen to see Hohenheim, deliver Trisha's message for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.90,0:10:30.71,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.71,0:10:32.24,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Ed! I...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.24,0:10:34.70,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,You stay hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.23,0:10:41.51,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,I'll come home after putting an end to everything on the Promised Day, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.24,0:10:44.24,Default,Ed,0000,0000,0000,,...wait for us with a freshly-baked apple pie. Deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.31,0:10:48.09,Default,Winry,0000,0000,0000,,Deal!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.16,0:10:59.97,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Work today took forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.15,0:11:03.44,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,But hey, is this really what we should be focusing on right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.05,0:11:05.60,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,The Promised Day is coming up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.78,0:11:07.32,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Not much else we can do!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.76,0:11:09.81,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor Marcoh and Scar haven't met up with us yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.53,0:11:13.15,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,Geez... where the hell are they?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.97,0:11:18.46,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.46,0:11:19.86,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, it's you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.16,0:11:22.41,Default,Jerso,0000,0000,0000,,"Hey, it's you guys"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.41,0:11:24.40,Default,Jerso,0000,0000,0000,,Where have you two been all this time?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.33,0:11:26.41,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.62,0:11:29.30,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,Let's head over to Central.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.04,0:11:35.51,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,But something feels a little off.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.51,0:11:40.55,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,We used to be soldiers, but now we're working with an Ishbalan.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.55,0:11:41.86,Default,Jer,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah it does.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.45,0:11:46.05,Default,Jer,0000,0000,0000,,For us, Amestris is our birthplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.05,0:11:47.51,Default,Jer,0000,0000,0000,,We've got family here as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.69,0:11:55.11,Default,Jer,0000,0000,0000,,But Scar, who used to rebel against the nation, is now working to protect it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.11,0:11:56.88,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get the wrong idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.88,0:11:59.07,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,My goal is not to protect this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.07,0:12:00.03,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,I'm working to change it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.42,0:12:05.92,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,I'm working in order for the people of this country to recognize the existence of the Ishbalans,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.92,0:12:09.95,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,a race that they denied.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.39,0:12:14.96,Default,Master,0000,0000,0000,,In order to change the world,\Nyou must start by changing yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.43,0:12:19.42,Default,Master,0000,0000,0000,,That's how it is, Amestrians.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.67,0:12:21.00,Default,Jer,0000,0000,0000,,Ishbalans?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.00,0:12:21.93,Default,Zam,0000,0000,0000,,Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.49,0:12:26.72,Default,Marcoh,0000,0000,0000,,We weren't just dawdling about for months doing nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.97,0:12:30.75,Default,Scar,0000,0000,0000,,They're comrades who share our goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.98,0:12:47.50,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,May this year's exercises be productive as always, Lieutenant General.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.12,0:12:53.11,Default,Grum,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad we're doing it in the east this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.65,0:12:56.58,Default,Grum,0000,0000,0000,,Joint exercises in the north are pretty tough for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.55,0:13:03.52,Default,Grum,0000,0000,0000,,Everything's ready on our end.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.31,0:13:05.92,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Ours, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.45,0:13:09.55,Default,Grum,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, a little problem has popped up...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.03,0:13:12.10,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,That being?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.41,0:13:19.69,Default,Grum,0000,0000,0000,,Little miss Bradley is here to observe as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.34,0:13:29.46,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,I was expecting someone high up to watch over the practice, since it's right before the Promised Day...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.93,0:13:33.84,Default,Grum,0000,0000,0000,,We'll just have to figure something out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.92,0:13:54.29,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,There it is again...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.64,0:14:02.77,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,The delay between visions is gradually getting shorter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.96,0:14:05.19,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I have to hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.56,0:14:07.74,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I need to get my body back, or...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.58,0:14:23.41,Default,Glut,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I can smell him!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.41,0:14:26.97,Default,Glut,0000,0000,0000,,Smells like the Fullmetal Alchemist's little brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.83,0:14:29.97,Default,Glut,0000,0000,0000,,Running away?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.52,0:14:33.37,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't good!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.93,0:14:36.43,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,I'm in no condition to fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.04,0:14:56.95,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,What's... this...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.97,0:15:04.89,Default,Al,0000,0000,0000,,Talk about great timing...!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.84,0:15:22.85,Default,Selim,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to have you keep quiet until the Promised Day,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.49,0:15:25.44,Default,Selim,0000,0000,0000,,Alphonse Elric.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.10,0:15:46.17,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Good evening, Major General.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.92,0:15:51.13,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I've got no tea for the likes of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.41,0:15:59.03,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,I may be able to take you out for dinner soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.03,0:16:01.81,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,So you finally plan to fulfill the promise from forever ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.82,0:16:10.82,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,{\fscx95}'Large' doesn't even begin to describe this mansion.\NThe wealth of the Armstrong family never ceases to amaze me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.74,0:16:15.82,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,You could fit a company... no, even a full battalion in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.65,0:16:20.83,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,If something may happen to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.53,0:16:25.04,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,you can have the entire mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.04,0:16:27.28,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,It won't fit into my coffin, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.53,0:16:30.67,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,You're not going to give it to your brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.11,0:16:38.22,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I'd say you're the better choice... by a hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.61,0:16:41.10,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,That's quite an honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.83,0:16:46.16,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Belatedly...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.57,0:16:49.48,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,This is to congratulate you for becoming the head of the Armstrong family.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.78,0:16:55.16,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,Hyacinths...?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.12,0:17:03.54,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,"Selim Bradley is a Homunculus."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.18,0:17:08.63,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Are you aware of what the Hyacinth represents?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.55,0:17:11.50,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.30,0:17:14.92,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Feminine beauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.20,0:17:18.65,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need your flowers!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.69,0:17:23.73,Default,Roy,0000,0000,0000,,Well, if you'll excuse me, Major General.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.43,0:17:28.69,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,You amateur.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.74,0:17:51.78,Default,Grum,0000,0000,0000,,This is annoying.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.78,0:17:56.87,Default,Grum,0000,0000,0000,,We should just aim a cannon at Bradley's tower and be done with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.87,0:17:58.13,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,Please don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.53,0:17:59.47,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Major Miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.74,0:18:04.97,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,So we still don't have a clue as to where Alphonse Elric disappeared to...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.97,0:18:08.14,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. We're still searching, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.14,0:18:11.16,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be that he was captured?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.66,0:18:16.24,Default,Miles,0000,0000,0000,,And the Promised Day is tomorrow...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.36,0:18:19.25,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Sire.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.90,0:18:22.28,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Major General Hakuro has arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.12,0:18:27.27,Default,Haku,0000,0000,0000,,Sire, there's something I need to inform you about Lieutenant General Grumman-
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.27,0:18:29.81,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,A coup d'etat using the Eastern army?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.31,0:18:32.79,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,We've already planned for such eventualities.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.22,0:18:37.26,Default,Haku,0000,0000,0000,,No, the joint practice is a bait.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.06,0:18:42.05,Default,Haku,0000,0000,0000,,The Ishbalan remnants will commit a terrorist act in Central,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.05,0:18:44.35,Default,Haku,0000,0000,0000,,now that defenses have weakened since Your Highness is here in the east.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.93,0:18:50.81,Default,Haku,0000,0000,0000,,Lieutenant General Grumman will use "terrorist suppression" as a pretense to invade Central.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.54,0:18:54.32,Default,Haku,0000,0000,0000,,He's planning on taking advantage of the confusion to take over Central Headquarters,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.96,0:18:56.94,Default,Haku,0000,0000,0000,,with the help of Colonel Mustang.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.03,0:19:09.52,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Just as Major General Hakuro stated,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.52,0:19:14.79,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,many Ishbalans have infiltrated Central vicinity over the past few days.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.11,0:19:26.25,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,I'm returning to Central.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.25,0:19:27.68,Default,Brad,0000,0000,0000,,I'll leave matters here in your hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.96,0:19:28.85,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.19,0:19:38.00,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,That damned Mustang... planning something outrageous.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.56,0:19:42.53,Default,Sol2,0000,0000,0000,,I thought we took care of him when we\Nseparated him from all of his useful men...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.28,0:19:55.31,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,The train stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.03,0:19:57.04,Default,Sol2,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.31,0:20:01.49,Default,Sol2,0000,0000,0000,,Sheep crossing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.49,0:20:03.38,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit, we're in a rush for time...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.93,0:20:13.94,Default,Sol2,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, they just left us!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.94,0:20:14.81,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.03,0:20:16.08,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.08,0:20:17.82,Default,Sol,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Make him stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.32,0:20:38.68,Default,Char,0000,0000,0000,,The sheep on the tracks have been exterminated.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.68,0:20:41.26,Default,Char,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be heading to Central as planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.49,0:20:43.49,Default,Char,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.49,0:20:44.78,Default,Char,0000,0000,0000,,The Colonel is awaiting our arrival.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.78,0:20:45.93,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.28,0:20:47.29,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.31,0:20:53.77,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,You played right into their hands, Major General Hakuro.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.63,0:20:59.11,Default,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,The train that was carrying the Führer President has been bombed!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.28,0:20:59.98,Default,Haku,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.03,0:21:16.68,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Everything begins tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.68,0:21:18.38,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Time to make our move,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.84,0:21:20.88,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,Second Lieutenant Breda, Master Sergeant Fuery.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.39,0:21:23.29,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,No need for the "Second Lieutenant", ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.91,0:21:25.80,Default,Breda,0000,0000,0000,,We're just plain old deserters now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.12,0:21:28.47,Default,Fuery,0000,0000,0000,,There goes my future...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.08,0:21:34.08,Default,Hawk,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have the Colonel take responsibility after everything's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.34,0:23:10.61,Default,Kle,0000,0000,0000,,The Führer President?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.86,0:23:13.07,Default,Fox,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way King Bradley could die...!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.44,0:23:15.76,Default,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,We can't make assumptions just yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.76,0:23:17.33,Default,Fox,0000,0000,0000,,What has the investigation turned up?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.33,0:23:19.23,Default,Kle,0000,0000,0000,,The squadron has yet to reach the scene of the accident!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.23,0:23:21.66,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,As soon as their leader is gone, this happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.45,0:23:20.64,Default-alt,Guy,0000,0000,0000,,Make them hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.64,0:23:21.67,Default-alt,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,Quit yelling!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.66,0:23:22.18,Default-alt,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,{\alpha&HFF&}PLACEHOLDER
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.66,0:23:23.30,Default-alt,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,This is not my job!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.58,0:23:24.34,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, they're nothing but an undisciplined mob.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.30,0:23:24.14,Default-alt,Guy2,0000,0000,0000,,But...!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.14,0:23:26.52,Default-alt,Guy3,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't the time for this!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.52,0:23:29.83,Default-alt,Guy3,0000,0000,0000,,{\alpha&HFF&}PLACEHOLDER
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.52,0:23:28.80,Default-alt,Guy3,0000,0000,0000,,The supreme commander is missing!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.80,0:23:29.98,Default-alt,Harri,0000,0000,0000,,I know that!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.98,0:23:31.51,Default,Oli,0000,0000,0000,,This may be my chance...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.73,0:23:40.56,Default,Frank,0000,0000,0000,,I never expected someone as important as you to visit this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.81,0:23:44.12,Default,Father,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.59,0:23:52.84,Default,Father,0000,0000,0000,,I'm still here.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.90,0:23:59.54,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,What lurks in the shadows?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.87,0:24:03.27,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Demons? Beasts? Monsters?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.03,0:24:09.51,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,A black gust of wind saves our heroes who are faced with a crisis.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.72,0:24:15.01,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Next time, Fullmetal Alchemist:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.01,0:24:18.63,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 47, Messenger of Darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.61,0:24:24.62,Default,Nar,0000,0000,0000,,Shed light on the heart of man. To an engulfing darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.62,0:24:26.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
